## 🔧 Complete Hardware Setup

The prototype consists of **five STM32F446RE Nucleo boards**, each functioning as an independent Electronic Control Unit (ECU) connected over the CAN Bus.

Each ECU performs a dedicated task:

- **ECU-1:** MPU6050 (Accelerometer & Gyroscope)
- **ECU-2:** DHT11 (Temperature & Humidity)
- **ECU-3:** DS18B20 Temperature Sensor
- **ECU-4:** Speed ECU (Raw Speed Data)
- **ECU-5:** Receiver ECU

The Receiver ECU collects telemetry from all sensor nodes and forwards validated CAN frames to the Raspberry Pi 5 for Ethernet transmission.

